<p>Across all of it, three rules matter most for a Border Collie: <strong>feed the brain early</strong> with real marine DHA, because the build window is short and the breed's whole gift depends on it; <strong>fuel the engine honestly</strong>, feeding to condition and erring toward enough rather than too little for a dog whose wiry frame hides its workload; and <strong>keep the minerals balanced</strong> (no calcium supplements unless your vet says so) with omega-3 for the joints and eyes. Because the breed is prone to hip dysplasia and inherited eye conditions, mention any limping, stiffness or vision concerns to your vet, and ask about eye screening — these are worth catching early.</p>

